de.mcp.cutcad.printdialog.lasercutter

Class LaserCutter

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mcp.cutcad.printdialog.lasercutter.LaserCutter

  • public class LaserCutter
extends java.lang.Object
    This class emulates an enum class of several lasercutters. Processing does not support the use of enum data types. This class has the probability to return the bed width/height of the lasercutter and the possible dpi settings.

      • LaserCutter

        public LaserCutter(java.lang.String device)
        Creates a new enum emulator and sets the selected lasercutter to match the parameter of this method. If the lasercutter in the parameter is not existent or not supported no lasercutter is selected.
        Parameters:
        device - The selected lasercutter is set to this value

      • LaserCutter

        public LaserCutter()
        Creates a new enum emulator and sets the selected lasercutter to none selected

    • Method Detail

      • returnDevice

        public java.lang.String returnDevice()
        Returns the name of the selected lasercutter. If no lasercutter was selected or a non existing one was selected, this method returns "no selected"
        Returns:
        the name of the selected lasercutter

      • returnDeviceNumber

        public int returnDeviceNumber()
        Return the number associated with the selected lasercutter. If no lasercutter was selected or a non existing one was selected, this method returns -1.
        Returns:
        number associated with the selected lasercutter

      • setDevice

        public void setDevice(java.lang.String device)
        Sets the selected lasercutter to the value of the parameter. If the lasercutter in the parameter is not existent or not supported the value is set to -1.
        Parameters:
        device - the lasercutter to be selected

      • setDevice

        public void setDevice(int device)
        Sets the selected lasercutter to the lasercutter associated with the int value of the parameter. To set select no lasercutter, calls this method with parameter value -1. When a value corresponding to no lasercutter is provided, the selected lasercutter is set to no selected (-1).
        Parameters:
        device - the number associated with the lasercutter to be selected
